  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 7.34,
      "text": "In crafting, value lives in the object, you protect the object, losing the chair is losing everything."
    },
    {
      "start": 8.8,
      "end": 17.18,
      "text": "In molding, value lives in the specification, the mold, the plastic part, disposable, regenerated at will."
    },
    {
      "start": 18.46,
      "end": 25.68,
      "text": "This is prompt-driven development. The prompt is your mold, the code is just plastic."
    },
    {
      "start": 26.88,
      "end": 34.5,
      "text": "No one nay, ninety-sil, hum, no one nay, no one nay, the Bruce is bearer."
    },
    {
      "start": 35.38,
      "end": 41.12,
      "text": "Now, let's get precise, because prompt is the mold is a nice metaphor, but it's incomplete."
    },
    {
      "start": 43.32,
      "end": 49.22,
      "text": "In PDD, the mold has three components, three types of capital you're accumulating."
    },
    {
      "start": 50.56,
      "end": 54.02,
      "text": "First tests, tests are the walls of your mold."
    },
    {
      "start": 54.8,
      "end": 59.24,
      "text": "Each test is a constraint, a boundary the generated code cannot cross."
    },
    {
      "start": 60.82,
      "end": 67.24,
      "text": "When the model generates code, it sees these tests, the code it produces must pass them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 67.6,
      "end": 70.7,
      "text": "it literally cannot generate code that violates these walls."
    },
    {
      "start": 72.06,
      "end": 75.94,
      "text": "Now, here's where it gets interesting, when you find a bug,"
    },
    {
      "start": 77.02,
      "end": 80.28,
      "text": "you don't patch the code, you add a wall."
    },
    {
      "start": 81.46,
      "end": 90.8,
      "text": "That wall is permanent, that bug can never occur again, not in this generation, not in any future generation."
    },
    {
      "start": 92.5,
      "end": 98.48,
      "text": "This is the ratchet effect, tests only accumulate, the mold only gets more precise,"
    },
    {
      "start": 99.06,
      "end": 101.98,
      "text": "each wall you add constrains all future generations."
    },
    {
      "start": 104.2,
      "end": 107.5,
      "text": "In traditional development, a bug fix helps one place."
    },
    {
      "start": 107.5,
      "end": 111.94,
      "text": "In PDD, a test prevents that bug everywhere, forever."
    }
  ]
}